OL,6,FTheir lawyers argued the religious
OL,7,Feducation and collective worship in
OL,8,Fthe school contravened their human
OL,9,Frights requiring the state to provide
OL,10,Feducation to "respect the right of
OL,11,Fparents to ensure such education is in
OL,12,Fconformity with their own religious
OL,13,Fand philosophical convictions".
OL,15,FThe High Court in Belfast found in
OL,16,Ffavour of the family in 2022 and said
OL,17,Fthe Christian RE taught and collective
OL,18,Fworship in schools in Northern Ireland
OL,19,Fis unlawful.
OL,26,@rD@NOUuD@^O]
